{%- comment -%}
  GitHub daily-contribution heatmap (past year).
  Hotlinks a live SVG from ghchart.rshah.org, themed in the site's
  purple. Image refreshes on every page load against current GitHub
  data — no build-time snapshot.

  Usage:
    {% include github_heatmap.liquid %}

  Reads site.github_username. Click-through goes to the profile.

  NOTE: the <a>/<img> tags below are kept on a single line on purpose.
  When Prettier split them across lines, kramdown (Jekyll's Markdown
  parser) stopped recognising them as a block-level HTML element and
  the raw source started rendering as plain text on /github/. The
  `<!-- prettier-ignore -->` directive keeps the next `prettier --write`
  sweep from reintroducing that break.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- if site.github_username -%}
  <p class="text-muted" style="font-size: 0.85rem; margin-bottom: 0.6rem;">
    Daily commit heatmap from my <a href="https://github.com/{{ site.github_username }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub profile</a>,
    past year.
  </p>
  <!-- prettier-ignore -->
  <a href="https://github.com/{{ site.github_username }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" aria-label="GitHub contribution graph for {{ site.github_username }}"><img src="https://ghchart.rshah.org/7047eb/{{ site.github_username }}" alt="GitHub contribution heatmap — 52 weeks of daily activity" loading="lazy" style="width: 100%; max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block;"></a>
{%- endif -%}
